name: AgroPortal
description: AgroPortal is a vocabulary and ontology repository for agronomy and related domains. It hosts ontologies, thesauri, and terminologies for agriculture, food, and environment.

name: AGROVOC
description: Maintained by the FAO (UN), this is a massive multilingual thesaurus covering agriculture, forestry, fisheries, food, and related environmental concepts.

name: BnF
description: The National Library of France. It hosts RAMEAU, the primary subject heading authority for French libraries, along with extensive concepts regarding authors, works, and periods.

name: Cordis Datalab
description: EU's research and innovation database. Contains information about EU-funded research projects, participants, publications, and results from Framework Programmes (FP7, Horizon 2020, Horizon Europe).

name: data.europa.eu
description: The official open data portal of the European Union. Contains EU authority tables (languages, countries, corporate bodies) and EuroVoc thesaurus.

name: DBpedia
description: The semantic extraction of Wikipedia. It serves as a general knowledge hub, defining millions of entities and concepts that are linked to external thesauri (like YAGO or Wikidata).

name: ERA Data Interop
description: European Union Agency for Railways data interoperability platform. Contains SKOS vocabularies for railway infrastructure, vehicle types, and operational concepts.

name: EU Publications Office
description: The CELLAR repository of the EU Publications Office. It hosts EU Vocabularies including EuroVoc, corporate bodies, countries, languages, and other authority tables used across EU institutions.

name: Fedlex
description: The official publishing platform for Swiss federal law. It exposes the Classified Compilation of legislation as a hierarchical concept scheme, allowing navigation through Swiss legal domains (Systematic Collection of Federal Law).

name: Finto - Finnish Thesaurus and Ontology Service
description: Finto is a Finnish thesaurus and ontology service providing access to vocabularies used in Finland, including YSO (General Finnish Ontology) and other domain-specific vocabularies.

name: Getty Vocabularies
description: The Getty Research Institute's Linked Open Data vocabularies including AAT (Art & Architecture Thesaurus), TGN (Thesaurus of Geographic Names), and ULAN (Union List of Artist Names).

name: Legilux
description: The official legal portal of the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg. It provides access to legislation and the 'Memorial' (official journal) using a structured legal vocabulary.

name: Linked Open Vocabularies
description: LOV (Linked Open Vocabularies) is a catalog of reusable vocabularies for the semantic web. It indexes vocabularies for describing datasets, services, and knowledge.

name: NERC Vocabulary Server
description: Managed by the British Oceanographic Data Centre. It provides standard vocabularies for oceanography and earth sciences, used globally to tag marine data.

name: STW Thesaurus for Economics
description: The STW Thesaurus for Economics is a comprehensive vocabulary for economics and business studies, maintained by ZBW - Leibniz Information Centre for Economics.

name: UNESCO Thesaurus
description: The UNESCO Thesaurus is a controlled vocabulary covering education, culture, natural sciences, social and human sciences, communication and information.
